Nyandarua needs a woman senator who is a good listener, courageous and God-fearing, human rights defender and Women Political Alliance director Beatrice Kamau has saidShe is running for the county Senate seat.Kamau said a woman is better placed to deal with the perennial bickering and foster unity among leaders and residents of Nyandarua.&ldquo;I am that woman. I will listen to what our children are saying and communicate to the governor. I will listen to the MCAs and other leaders. I will sit and reason with them,&rdquo; she said.